originalText.text: I recently booked a treatment session with Dr. Lee to address the lower back pain I was experiencing.  After my treatment session with Dr. Lee my back pain improved immensely.  I highly recommend Dr. Lee.

originalText.text: Dr. Lee is a great Acupuncturist! She is communicative and attentive to your health goals. I strongly recommend her practice! She has helped reduce my pain and worked with me to achieve great results in just a couple of visits. Dr. Lee is knowledgeable, professional and patient. I am glad that I was able to find her through my chiropractor Dr. Pico.

originalText.text: Dr. Lee is great. I wasn't sure if acupuncture was going to help my knee pain, but it has definitely done so. The experience hasn't been what I'd expected -- I'd had other acupuncture sessions that were less clinical, and less effective. Dr. Lee's knows what she's doing, she very perceptive, and careful and methodical about her work. She's also reassuring and helpful in getting you to describe what's wrong so she can treat it well; in other words, everything I want in a doctor.

originalText.text: Sciatica is no longer mine I gave it away when I came here! Two sessions for treatment was what I needed and I hate I didn’t come sooner but I’m happy I chose Dr. Lee! She was such a great listener, knowledgeable and informative. Took her time with my treatment and I can’t wait to return for further care. Definitely recommended!

originalText.text: Dr. Erin Lee is awesome. Had acupuncture in the past but Dr. Lee takes it to another level. She asked questions about my health and carefully assessed my needs and explained/educated me on the underlying reasons for each procedure performed. She has a full array of tools from acupuncture, cupping and sound/vibration therapy. i pulled a hamstring and she helped me recover relatively quickly. Her facilities are in a clean and professional medical office. Highly recommend her practice!
